        <h2 id="honey-pizza">Goat Cheese and Honey Pizza</h2>
        <!-- Source: this one time, I had a pizza like this in Paris, and it was totally delicious, so I made it again at home. Except by "I", I mean my BF. Also, the one in France had an egg on it, and I do not do that at home. -->
        
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Kartoffel_pizza_%28with_border%29.jpg/332px-Kartoffel_pizza_%28with_border%29.jpg" alt="This is definitely not my pizza" width="300">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 3 hours total</li>
            <li>Serves: 8 slices</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Pizza Dough</td>
                    <td>Enough</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Goat cheese</td>
                    <td>Small log</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sweet onion</td>
                    <td>One</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Honey</td>
                    <td>Plenty</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Arugula</td>
                    <td>Small bunch</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Butter or oil</td>
                    <td>2 Tbsp, for onions</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Make dough.
</p>

        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Pre-cook dough, most of the way through. Meanwhile, chop and carmelize onions on stovetop using butter/oil. 
</p>

        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Top with crubmled goat cheese, stir fried onions, and honey.
</p>

        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Cook until done. Just before finishing, pull out and top with arugula. Place in oven just until arugula wilts. Remove, allow to cool somewhat before cutting and serving.
</p>
    
    <h2 id="rosemary-chicken">Rosemary Chicken Breast</h2>
        
