        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Pretty sure you start by trimming the chicken, which is the worst.
</p>

        <p> <strong>Step 2:</strong> Then I guess you probably cook it on the stovetop? Oil, salt, pepper, add the rosemary?</p>
        
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> When it's almost done, add the cream into the pan. You probably should have started the couscous on another burner by now, BTW. Finish cooking the chicken.
        </p>

        <p>
            <strong>Step 4:</strong> Finish the couscous and put it in a shallow bowl or on a plate, I guess. Spoon some of the cream over the top, and place a chicken breast on it.
        </p>
        
        <p>
            <strong>Step 5:</strong> Okay, so, I'm pretty sure I'm forgetting some of the ingredients and at least some of the steps, but... c'est la vie.
        </p>
        
        <h2 id="coffee">Iced Coffee</h2>
        
        <!-- Remember how I said I can't cook? This is what I'm reduced to.-->
        
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Blue_Bottle%2C_Kyoto_Style_Ice_Coffee_%285909775445%29.jpg/330px-Blue_Bottle%2C_Kyoto_Style_Ice_Coffee_%285909775445%29.jpg" alt="Not actually <em>my</em> iced coffee, but I'm pretty sure it all looks the same" width="300">
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 8+ hours</li>
            <li>Serves: 3</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Coffee grounds</td>
                    <td>1.75 oz</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Water</td>
                    <td>3-4 cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Creamer</td>
                    <td>Lots</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Milk</td>
                    <td>Enough</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Put the cofee grounds in the French press. You don't have a French press? Buy one.
</p>

        <p> <strong>Step 2:</strong> Pour 1-2 C room-temperature water over the grounds. Stir or slosh them around to make sure all of the grounds are mixed in to the water. Add the remaining water once you're sure there are no pockets of dried grounds.
        </p>
        
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Wait. For like, 8-12 hours, keeping the French press full of delicious future coffee at room temp.
        </p>

        <p>
            <strong>Step 4:</strong> Gently and slowly depress the plunger on the French press. If you do it quickly, it'll spit coffee out the spout. It's actually really funny.
        </p>
        
        <p>
            <strong>Step 5:</strong> Pour the coffee into a glass. Add creamer and milk to taste. Enjoy!
        </p>
        
